// ks2WordData.js — KS2 Spelling Word Database v26 (post-curriculum-gap-close)
// Y3/4: 1852 words (109 statutory)
// Y5/6: 1065 words (105 statutory)
// Total: 2917 words
// Difficulty: easy=1202 medium=730 hard=985
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// AUDIT, REVIEW & CURRICULUM-GAP-CLOSE LOG — v23 → v26
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
// v23 → v24: 8-pass audit + Passes A/B/C remediation
// v24 → v25: focused review pass on Pass A judgement calls
// v25 → v26: BATCH 26 — closing curriculum gaps identified by coverage check
//
// ─── BATCH 26 (v25 → v26) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Coverage check against the app's curriculumLists.js identified 92 words used
// in curated lessons that v25 did not cover (81.3% coverage). Batch 26 closes
// those gaps with 61 new KS2 words across five clusters:
//
//   1. Y3 -ough family (7): bought, plough, borough, bough, dough,
//      thoroughly, throughout — silent letter group
//   2. Y3 i-before-e words (5): receive, deceive, niece, relieve, yield —
//      spelling pattern group
//   3. Y3 other (8): sword, whistle, unwell, unclear, reuse, repay, disorder,
//      + Y3 -tion family (nation, passion, caption, fraction, option)
//   4. Y5 British -our endings (15): favour, labour, behaviour, glamour,
//      flavour, humour, vapour, armour, clamour, harbour, odour, rumour,
//      savour, tumour, vigour — NEW PATTERN GROUP: 'british ending'
//   5. Y5 Greek roots (9): symphony, philosophy, technology, mythology,
//      chronology, bibliography, thermometer, diameter, polygon — academic
//      language / science groups
//   6. Y5 French loanwords (13): chauffeur, ballet, bouquet, crochet, debris,
//      critique, naive, niche, regime, silhouette, resume, brochure, fiancé
//      — NEW PATTERN GROUP: 'loanword'
//
// Companion batch in KS1 v13 (32 words) closes the Y1/Y2 phonics edge cases:
//   • Y1 short-vowel CVC/CCVC words: cow, tick, flick, flock, bud, fan, hip,
//     nap, rib, sob, tug, hull, pill
//   • Y2 oo/ai/ay/-ight/wh- words: hoop, noon, root, soot, drain, gain, grain,
//     spray, goes, fright, blight, plight, starlight, twilight, flashlight,
//     wheat, whistle, whatever, whichever
//
// ─── AUDIT FINDINGS (against v23) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
//   • ~570 words ending in suffix patterns mistagged outside 'suffix' group
//   • 21 words had self-references in their relatedWords arrays
//   • 3 words had duplicate values within their relatedWords array
//   • 28 words tagged Y5/6 'easy' were Y3/4-level vocabulary
//   • 35 words appearing in both KS1 and KS2 had divergent definitions
//   • 1,511 entries had no commonMistakes value
//   • Taught-pattern groups had inconsistent corePatternWord coverage
//   • All entries had definitions.ages7to10, sentence, wordType, spellingRule ✓
//   • Y5/6 entries correctly leave definitions.ages5to7 empty by convention ✓
//
// ─── PASS A: Pattern group retag ───────────────────────────────────────────────
//   184 words moved into 'suffix' group; suffix grew 163 → 347 entries
//   Y5/6 suffix coverage: 92 → 207 entries
//   Conservative ruleset protected statutory, homophone, science, history,
//   nature and emotion groups; excluded -ment words from suffix tagging
//
// ─── PASS B: Data cleanup ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   • Removed 21 self-references from relatedWords arrays
//   • Removed duplicates within 3 relatedWords arrays
//   • Reclassified 28 misplaced Y5/6 'easy' words back to Y3/4
//   • Resolved 35 KS1/KS2 definition mismatches (kept longer definition)
//
// ─── PASS C: Optional enrichment ───────────────────────────────────────────────
//   • C1: Marked 282 additional taught-pattern words as corePatternWord;
//     all six taught-pattern groups now at 100% core coverage
//   • C2: Generated commonMistakes for 359 previously-empty entries using
//     pattern-based heuristics; coverage rose from 47% → 60%
//
// ─── REVIEW PASS (v24 → v25) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   Q1: 9 -ent root words moved to suffix (silent, silence, student, agent,
//       president, ingredient, nutrient, continent, current)
//   Q2: 5 -ous words moved to suffix for consistency (ambiguous, meticulous,
//       cavernous, ominous, treacherous)
//   Q3: 2 false positives reverted (dreary, weary — ends in 'ary' but root is
//       drear/wear and the suffix is -y, not -ary)
//
// ─── FINAL STATE (v26) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//   Total KS2 words: 2917 (Y3/4: 1852; Y5/6: 1065)
//   Suffix group: 364 entries
//   New pattern groups: 'british ending' (15), 'loanword' (13)
//   commonMistakes coverage: 1765/2917 (60.5%)
//   corePatternWord coverage: 1480/2917 (50.7%)
//   Coverage against curriculumLists.js: expected ~98%+ post-integration
//
// ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

